# grapher_home_return_smoke.numos — Phase 9F return-to-launcher reliability guard.
# Presses HOME (MODE) from EVERY Grapher state — Expressions, Graph, Table, Trace,
# Templates modal, and mid-edit — and asserts we land back at the launcher each time,
# re-entering the Grapher between checks. Before 9F (deferred teardown in NativeHal)
# this hung in lv_timer_handler on the first return. Assert-only; NOT CI-gated.
log "home_return: baseline launcher"
wait 180
assert_app Menu
# 1) HOME from Expressions
key graph
wait 40
assert_app Grapher
key home
wait 50
assert_app Menu
# 2) HOME from Graph tab
key graph
wait 30
key graph
wait 40
key home
wait 50
assert_app Menu
# 3) HOME from Table tab
key graph
wait 30
key table
wait 40
key home
wait 50
assert_app Menu
# 4) HOME from Trace (commit y=x, Graph tab, ENTER toggles trace -> POI timer)
key graph
wait 30
key down
key enter
key x
key enter
wait 30
key graph
wait 30
key enter
wait 40
key home
wait 50
assert_app Menu
# 5) HOME from Templates modal (add empty slot, RIGHT opens templates)
key graph
wait 30
key down
key enter
key right
wait 40
key home
wait 50
assert_app Menu
# 6) HOME mid-edit (partial expression, never committed)
key graph
wait 30
key down
key enter
key x
key home
wait 50
assert_app Menu
# 7) re-entry still works after all that
key graph
wait 40
assert_app Grapher
key home
wait 40
assert_app Menu
log "home_return: PASS - HOME returns to launcher from all states + re-entry works"
